The Problem:
Once enrolled in a program, students receive a course plan. However, still many choices remain: 
can I switch to core courses in a different order to the plan? Which electives should I take? 
Which major and courses should I take for specific career paths?

Challenge: 
The challenge is to innovate a software-based solution to help students to navigate selection of majors, courses, etc., 
throughout various stages of their degree program.

Our (Potential) Solution(s):
Instead of students using a course plan to organise their courses, we can create a software algorithm 
that automatically enrols students in courses according to the course plan. This minimizes the potential of 
enrolling in the incorrect courses, outside of the course plan, as students will no longer have to individually 
enrol in separate courses.
In the case of electives, students will be shown a drop down menu of eligible electives, limited depending on their degree,
number of electives, major, etc.

Hypothesis:
If students are provided with a software-based enrolment tool that automatically selects core courses according to 
their degree plan and restricts elective choices to only eligible options based on their program, major, 
and remaining requirements, then students will make fewer enrolment errors, and feel more informed on their education choices. 
